{{Infobox Organization |name = International Forum on Mood and Anxiety Disorders |image = |image_border = |size = |caption = International Forum on Mood and Anxiety Disorders |membership = |abbreviation = IFMAD |formation = 2000 |headquarters = [[Monaco]] ([[Principality of Monaco]]) |leader_title = Chairman |leader_name = [[:de:Siegfried Kasper|Siegfried Kasper]] |leader_title2 = Co-Chairman |leader_name2 = [[Stuart Montgomery]] |website = [http://www.ifmad.org ifmad.org] }}
The '''International Forum on Mood and Anxiety Disorders''' or '''IFMAD''' is a professional organisation dedicated to raising awareness of the latest international thinking and innovations in [[Mood (psychology)|mood]] and [[anxiety disorder]]s and promoting the exchange of ideas across the global [[Psychiatry|psychiatric]] community.
IFMAD was founded in 2000 by [[:de:Siegfried Kasper|Professor Siegfried Kasper]] and [[Stuart Montgomery|Professor Stuart Montgomery]], supported by a scientific committee consisting of leading figures in mood and anxiety disorders from around the world.
==Activities== IFMAD organises a yearly congress to promote debate and highlight the latest research in mood and anxiety disorders. The annual event has become an important forum for the exchange of ideas and a key part of the congress calendar.
